@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxOtpInput))]

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxOtpInput)">
	<DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
	<p>
		The component renders a series of single-character inputs and binds the concatenated code as a <code>string</code> <code>Value</code>.
		Focus advances automatically after entering a digit, <kbd>Backspace</kbd> in an empty field moves to the previous field,
		arrow keys navigate between the inputs, and pasting a full code distributes it across all inputs.
		The first input renders <code>autocomplete="one-time-code"</code> to support SMS/email code autofill.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo)" Tabs="false" />

	<DocHeading Title="Connected inputs" />
	<p>Set <code>Connected="true"</code> to visually connect the inputs into a single cohesive field (Bootstrap input group styles).</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo_Connected)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Four-digit PIN" />
	<p>
		Use the <code>Length</code> parameter to change the number of inputs, e.g. for shorter codes like 4-digit PINs.
		Set <code>Mask="true"</code> to use password fields hiding the entered digits.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo_Pin)" />

	<DocHeading Title="With separator" />
	<p>
		Use the <code>GroupSize</code> parameter to split the inputs into groups with a visual separator between them, creating grouped codes like <code>123–456</code>.
		The separator is purely visual&mdash;it does not affect the <code>Value</code>. Customize the separator text with the <code>Separator</code> parameter.
		Combined with <code>Connected="true"</code>, each group of inputs gets connected.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo_Separator)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Disabled" />
	<p>
		Set the <code>Enabled</code> parameter to <code>false</code> to prevent interaction
		(or use <a href="/components/HxFormState">HxFormState</a> to disable multiple controls at once).
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo_Disabled)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Completion event" />
	<p>The <code>OnCompleted</code> event is raised when all inputs are filled and receives the complete code (you can submit the form or start verifying the code right away).</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo_OnCompleted)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Validation" />
	<p>
		The component integrates with <code>EditForm</code> validation the same way as other form components.
		The validation state renders on the wrapping element (<code>is-invalid</code> class styles all the inputs).
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxOtpInput_Demo_Validation)" />
</ApiDoc>
